PART 1

While unzipping the zip folder please make sure you get three folders (amongst some pdf files): src, ner and pos
The working directory should be the folder containing these 3.

In order to run the code you will need to provide two parameters:
	1) indicates the test number (in our case test1)
	2) the data we are modeling (pos/ner)
An example for a correct command:
	python src/tagger1.py test1 pos
	
Relevant files:
1. tagger1.py (main code, training the model happens here).
2. utils.py (preprocessing the data, creating windows etc.).
################################################################################################################
PART 3:

While unzipping the zip folder please make sure you get three folders (amongst some pdf files): src, ner and pos
The working directory should be the folder containing these 3.

In order to run the code you will need to provide three parameters.
	1) indicates the test number (in our case test3)
	2) the data we are modeling (pos/ner)
	3) flag indicating we are willing to use pre-trained embeddings (pre)
An example for a correct command:
	python src/tagger1.py test3 pos pre
	
Relevant files:
1. tagger1.py (main code, training the model happens here).
2. utils.py (preprocessing the data, creating windows etc.).
################################################################################################################
PART 4:

While unzipping the zip folder please make sure you get three folders (amongst some pdf files): src, ner and pos
The working directory should be the folder containing these 3.

In order to run the code you will need to provide at least three parameters and no more than four.
	1) indicates the test number (in our case test4)
	2) the data we are modeling (pos/ner)
	3) flag indicating we are willing to use sub-words units (sub)
	4) flag indicating we are willing to use pre-trained embeddings (pre)
	(the 4th parameter is not obligatory, it's your choice)
An example for a correct command:
	python src/tagger1.py test4 pos sub pre
	
Relevant files:
1. tagger1.py (main code, training the model happens here).
2. utils.py (preprocessing the data, creating windows etc.).
################################################################################################################
